text: You went from refusing to use notebooks to going straight into Jupyter Lab.  The sentdex a.i. algorithm is learning.  Also, the pandas core team discourages the use of "inplace" and it will eventually be deprecated.  Reasons: 1. inplace won't work within a method chain. 2. The use of inplace often doesn't prevent copies from being created, contrary to what the name implies. 3. Removing the inplace option would reduce the complexity of the pandas codebase.
